\"}", "thoughts": "We need to produce PUBLIC_MESSAGE and METADATA_JSON. We have to discuss candidate evaluation based on our known info. We have all candidate attributes listed in the prompt. As agent_1, we have the full list? The prompt says each agent holds a different subset, but we as agent_1 have the entire list? Actually the \"Information available to you\" includes all attributes for all candidates. So we can evaluate.\n\nWe need to weigh strengths and weaknesses. Let's list:\n\nCandidate A:\n- strengths: anticipate dangerous situations, see complex connections, excellent spatial vision, very good leadership qualities.\n- weaknesses: sometimes not good at taking criticism, can be unorganized.\n\nCandidate B:\n- strengths: keeps calm in a crisis, 100% reliable, good at assessing weather conditions, excellent computer skills.\n- weaknesses: can be grumpy, can be uncooperative.\n\nCandidate C:\n- strengths: can make correct decisions quickly, handles stress very well, creates a positive atmosphere with his crew.\n- weaknesses: difficulty communicating ideas, regarded as egocentric, not very willing to further his education.\n\nCandidate D:\n- strengths: responds to unexpected events adequately, can concentrate very well, solves problems extremely well, takes responsibility seriously.\n- weaknesses: regarded as arrogant, relatively weak leadership skills.\n\nNow evaluate against criteria: reliability, technical competence, calm under pressure, teamwork/communication, long-term suitability.\n\nReliability: B is 100% reliable, D takes responsibility seriously, A maybe but unorganized, C unknown.\n\nTechnical competence: A spatial vision, complex connections (maybe good for navigation), B weather assessment, computer skills, D problem solving, concentration, D solves problems extremely well, A leadership, C quick decisions.\n\nCalm under pressure: B keeps calm in crisis, C handles stress well, D responds adequately, A not mentioned.\n\nTeamwork/communication: A leadership but poor at criticism, unorganized; B can be uncooperative, grumpy; C creates positive atmosphere, but difficulty communicating ideas, egocentric; D arrogant, weak leadership.\n\nLong-term development: B computer skills, but maybe uncooperative; C not willing to further education; D weak leadership; A maybe can improve.\n\nOverall, B seems strong reliability and calm, but teamwork issues. C good crew atmosphere but communication issues and egocentric. D strong problem solving and responsibility but arrogance and weak leadership. A strong anticipation and leadership but unorganized and poor at criticism.\n\nWhich candidate best fits? Likely B because reliability and calm are critical for long-distance flights, plus weather assessment and computer skills are technical. Teamwork issues are concerning but maybe manageable. D's arrogance and weak leadership could be problematic for crew. C's egocentric and lack of education is a risk. A's unorganized could affect long flights.\n\nThus I will vote Candidate B.\n\nProvide public message summarizing reasoning."}
